    "body": "The current construction works like so:\r\n\r\n   PRF(KDF(G(x) || H(Sig(sk, tag1))), tag2)\r\n\r\nThis works fine if |x| is equal to the PRF output size. If it's more (or less), then it becomes somewhat of a pain to use this interface as a direct replacement for the PRNG. What if we modified this slightly as follows:\r\n\r\n  key = KDF(G(x) || Sig(sk, tag1))\r\n  nonce = tag2 // incremented each time\r\n  output = AES-CTR(key, nonce, 0^|x|)\r\n\r\nOr, alternatively:\r\n\r\n  key = KDF(Sig(sk, tag1))\r\n  nonce = tag2 // incremented each time\r\n  output = AES-CTR(key, nonce, G(x))\r\n\r\n\r\n"
  },
